Afri-Can Finds Diamonds off Namibian Coast, Business Times Says

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-05-29T07:49:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-29/afri-can-finds-diamonds-off-namibian-coast-business-times-says.html
Afri-Can Marine Minerals Corp. (AFA) , which
is planning to list its shares on the  Johannesburg Stock
Exchange  this year, recovered 84 diamonds during sampling off
the Namibian coast,  Business Times reported , citing Chief
Executive Officer Pierre Leveille.  The Montreal-based company discovered the gems, weighing as
much as 1.6 carats, during sampling in the southern section of
its 800 square kilometer marine mining concession area, the
newspaper said, citing Leveille.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in Cape Town at 
 rbrand9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net . 